<div class="page">
  <div class="chapter-title">Chapter 5<br>Conclusion</div>
  <p class="justify">
    This chapter concludes the report by summarizing the major achievements of the project, acknowledging current limitations,
    and highlighting future work that can increase the value and readiness of the system.
  </p>

  <h2>Summary</h2>
  <p class="justify">
    Quiz Master is a complete mini lab project that demonstrates the design and development of a role-based mobile quiz platform using Flutter and Firebase.
    The project includes secure login and signup, admin-controlled settings, question bank management, exam and practice modes, result analytics, leaderboard
    support, progress visualization, and profile picture functionality. The current codebase reflects modern mobile engineering practices and is validated through
    successful static analysis and automated tests.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation</h2>
  <p class="justify">
    The project still has some limitations. It does not yet include advanced institutional features such as class-wise grouping, question import from files,
    PDF report export, push notifications, or teacher-side analytics dashboards beyond the existing leaderboard and progress views. The performance analysis is
    largely qualitative and code-based rather than benchmark-based. In addition, live profile image upload requires a properly configured Firebase Storage bucket
    during deployment.
  </p>

  <h2>Future Work</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Add teacher-side reporting export in PDF or spreadsheet format.</li>
    <li>Support batch, semester, course, and section-based grouping.</li>
    <li>Add question categories such as image-based MCQ, short answer, or descriptive evaluation.</li>
    <li>Implement stronger analytics, notification, and scheduling features.</li>
    <li>Expand Firebase Storage usage for richer profile customization and question media attachments.</li>
    <li>Introduce performance benchmarking and usage analytics for real deployment evaluation.</li>
  </ul>

